## Part A: Integration Fixes (Your Work)

> These are issues in the frontend integration layer that need fixing now.

### 🔴 FIX 1: Alert PATCH Status — Body vs Query Param

**Problem**: Frontend sends query param, but backend expects JSON body.

| File | Current (Broken) | 
|------|-----------------|
| [useAlerts.ts L108](file:///c:/Users/caleb_8h6kswm/Documents/GitHub/threatmatrix-ai/frontend/hooks/useAlerts.ts#L108) | `api.patch(\`/alerts/${id}/status?new_status=${newStatus}\`)` |
| [alerts.py L77-80](file:///c:/Users/caleb_8h6kswm/Documents/GitHub/threatmatrix-ai/backend/app/api/v1/alerts.py#L77-L80) | `body: StatusUpdateRequest` with `new_status: str` field |

**Fix** — Change frontend to send body:

```diff
// useAlerts.ts — updateStatus
- const { error: err } = await api.patch(`/api/v1/alerts/${id}/status?new_status=${newStatus}`);
+ const { error: err } = await api.patch(`/api/v1/alerts/${id}/status`, { new_status: newStatus });
```

